replies.body:
The teams are playing the strategy that works so that they can win, so if you don't think that the strategy is fun to watch, then don't watch it. It's not Riot's fault that you have certain tastes in what you like to watch, so please don't blame them.

For me, this Worlds has been very amusing to watch; seeing certain strategies (like different picks in the ADC/Mid/Top positions) and upsets make this one of the less one-sided Worlds in a long time. It cool seeing different iterations of a certain strategy. My favorite moment was when WE beat an ardent censor team fighting comp with an early-game siege comp. 

And Fizz coming out today is such a treat!{{sticker:sg-ahri-2}}
